author: COMSOL
description: This is a model of the Brüel and Kjær 4134 condenser microphone. The geometry and material parameters are those of the actual microphone. The modeled sensitivity level is compared to measurements performed on an actual microphone and shows good agreement. The membrane deformation, pressure, velocity, electric field are also determined. Finally, the mechanical-thermal noise floor is computed in postprocessing.
